<br>
1) Time consuming.  A lot of people in my guild don't have the playtime to fail repeatedly while working strategies out.<br>
<br>
2) Competition.  Other guilds tend to set time limits for our guild, or they like to take over the mob if we lose.<br>
<br>
Factoring in those two, we decide to bypass the extra time and competition by reading up on strategies to make our raiding more effective.  I don't see what's wrong with that, it's just using the resources available to you.<br>
<br>
I'm speaking from a lower-end guild though.. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=168753"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.pacbell.net/ping000/Rasc-sig.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=myrddinra>MyrddinRA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 337<br> <font color=#333333>(12/13/02 10:31:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm46.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=64>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://rifleman.free.fr/icon2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Re:Silliness</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Time consuming. A lot of people in my guild don't have the playtime to fail repeatedly while working strategies out.<br>
